[Cantaloupes are said to have a shelf life of 2 weeks or so. Since
Jensen Farms, the source of the contaminated melons, voluntarily
recalled these melons, which it says were shipped between 29 Jul and
10 Sep 2011, there should not be many more of these melons being
eaten. However, because the incubation period of listeriosis can be up
to a month or more, there may be more cases, deaths, miscarriages, or
stillbirths reported in the future due to consumption of these
_Listeria_-contaminated melons. - Mod.ML]
